##New Year's Eve in 18th-line county of Jiangxi Province: No one is immune from the times | Sandwich

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

This article describes the daily life of an 18th-line county in Jiangxi Province under the shadow of the new type of pneumonia: 0 Cases were diagnosed and people were in a state of panic. The more we try to be empathetic in these times, the more we try to understand the emotional impact that the average person feels in the face of this crisis. No link exists apart from the whole.

From The economist print edition

The entrance to the village has finally begun to hold back visitors.
On February 1st, 12 days after Academician Zhong Nanshan said there had been a "human-to-human" COVID-19, and nine days after Wuhan, a city of tens of millions, was declared closed, the 18th-line counties in Jiangxi Province, where I come from, were finally put on the worst possible alert.

When we drove up, the cordon was set up in front of Grandma's house. It was a three-story building that had just been built in 2016. At first, it had a walled courtyard. Later, someone said that "a new countryside" would be built here. Every household would be open and beautiful. So let's tear down the wall near the road, but agreed to plant a row of bushes along the road. In the yard, grandma still let the Person Plant Two sweet-scented Osmanthus trees.
I got out of the car and stepped forward to ask the inspector with the Red Armband how to sign in. I saw the single-person desk and chair, probably from the village primary school, with a paper written on it. There were lots of names and numbers on it, but it was hard to read. Maybe it's for questioning. There is also a gray temperature gun placed on the side, to the ear, you can detect the body temperature. But the man sitting there did not seem to want to talk to me, and did not answer a word. Another person, standing, shook his hand at me, indicating that he could go inside.
That's what I expected. Even in the most desperate times, the country is not a place to be completely impersonal. Even if they do not know me, but as long as I know that the first family in the village relatives, say a few words, will be released.
My grandmother was waiting in the yard, leaning on a cane.
1
The company originally gave us a long holiday early this year, so I took the high-speed train home with my mother on January 21.
Before this, I had heard news of "pneumonia" , but saw that all sides are still in the confirmation, has not been particularly alert. I brought home two masks from Shanghai, one for my mother. She saw more people wearing masks in the waiting room than usual, so she wore them for a while, but then she slipped them into her coat pocket and said she was not used to wearing them. I myself have been wearing a disposable mask since the beginning of the trip, from the high-speed railway, to the K-WORD train, to the county train station in front of the car battery, four or five hours have not taken off the road. But later, to see the online popular science realized that he put the white face of the mask outside, is wearing the wrong way. "If you wear it by mistake, there are more bacteria. "
But at the time, the family did not seem to be aware of the impending deluge of news. I took off my mask before I walked in the door and saw my family. I still had a thought in my mind, don't let my family think that this is the city people making a mountain out of a molehill.

2
I got a call from my cousin on New Year's Day twenty-nine. She works in a nearby township government, and in previous years she was mostly heard talking about how to meet poverty alleviation targets. Behind my grandmother's house was a neighborhood committee in the village. I had never seen anyone work there, but last year when the weather was fine, I went for a walk in the back and saw a message board standing over there, the names of the poverty-stricken people in one household and the names of the officials directly helping them are listed. This year, my cousin's voice was anxious and serious, and I could see her scowling at me and saying, "don't go out for a while. I'm not kidding. "
We exchanged some information, and I learned that she had heard that in a village in front of us, a doctor had been found returning home from Hubei Province, who had sneaked home in the last few days without even telling his family and relatives. It was possible that it was a suspected case, we're being quarantined. "If that person is diagnosed, I will have a lot of work to do this Spring Festival. "
I shouted this to the rest of the family. We were still preparing for the New Year at my grandmother's house, some in the kitchen, some playing Mahjong in the small room, some sitting in the Living Room Sofa watching TV.
Cousin's words have a certain authority. When the elders at home heard this, they began to feel that more attention should be paid to the problem. "No wonder I saw that Wuhan was about to close down. It wasn't like this when SARS was so serious. Is this more serious than SARS? ".
3
The next day, I went to the supermarket in the county. The reason is to buy some drinks for the New Year's Eve dinner.
My New Year's rule is first at Grandma's house, and relatives here to have dinner, and then go to grandma's house New Year's. Originally we both lived in the county, within walking distance of each other, but since grandma insisted on moving to the country, there was a gap of eight kilometers between us. I remembered that I hadn't seen a single bottle of hand sanitizer in my grandmother's bathroom the day before, so I stopped at the supermarket and bought several. On my way home, I went into the drugstore and asked, "do you still have the mask? "
The saleswoman in the white coat came up to me from the checkout counter, without her mask, and said, yes, there are three more of these gauze masks left. Do you want them
$3 A pop. I picked it up off the shelf. This mask consists of 24 layers of gauze, as described in shallow red letters on a thin plastic sheet. But I can clearly see the Mesh inside, I thought, if this face-to-face speech there are flying foam out, certainly can not block Ah. The shop assistant saw my hesitation and added, "the other masks were sold out a few days ago, and everyone rushed to buy them. "
Turns out not everyone is as late-bloomer as my family.
When I paid, I bought bottles of Aerosol alcohol. On the way back, I met my aunt who was coming back from the market. She gave her a bottle of alcohol. She looked at the transparent bottle as if it were a new thing. But she kept it and said she would use it.
4
At the same time, with the closure of the city of Wuhan, the daily information available on the Internet has begun to feel the events turning desperate. Some estimate that the outbreak could be 10 times more severe than SARS.
My deepest memory of SARS, or in the grandmother's home that no more than 10 square meters of living room, a small stove, smoked vinegar. The television screen was filled with Hu Jintao's speech, and through the nostrils crept a foul smell of vinegar. Grandma told me to just suck it up.
My cousin began to share the "ban" with me on wechat groups every day. No visits, no New Year greetings, no dinner, no playing Mahjong.
But I still live a "fluid" life every day, from my house in the county to my grandmother's house in the village.
I saw some stories of reconciliation with my family after the siege of Wuhan. In this special period, because can not go out, and let the small family pattern of family ties formed in modern China to fight the epidemic when people can hold on to the last rope of warmth, but there are families are embarrassed.
It took me a long time to admit that my father's family and my mother's family, like oil and water, were completely incompatible. They tried to live for many years, up to now there is no choice to separate, but oil or oil, water or water. During the holidays, my mother and I slept in the same bed, and my father snored next door. Every morning my mother woke up and thought about going to her grandmother's house, cooking or playing Mahjong or sitting in the yard eating sunflower seeds, but she didn't even want to eat breakfast in her own house. They are "family" in the traditional sense of the word, but the habits of life so many years do not mix. Fortunately, this is a better age for equal rights than it was 20 or 30 years ago, when women didn't have to revolve around men. My mother told me that she didn't want to go home for the Spring Festival either. But the thought of his mother, nearly 90 years old, always worry about their own may not accompany a few years, so to the new year pass, not only early decided to go home, but also to extend their holiday.
Because of the outbreak, my father and grandmother hardly went out. They often wear their own cotton pajamas, sometimes watching television, have time to play with a mobile phone, have time to sit in the yard sunbathing on the past. He didn't talk much either.
My mother and I "flow" almost daily, hitchhiking with the rest of our family to grandma's house. "Isn't it safer to drive your own family's car? We don't see anyone else. "
If you see someone on the street in the village, chances are they are not wearing a mask. Yeah, I guess so. You can't buy masks anymore.
In response to my "floating" population, my cousin and I said that they planned to put up banners in villages and towns to warn and admonish.
I sent her a group to see a city in the northwest in the street corner hanging "New Year is harmful, dinner is sent to death, " the picture, please if they really want to do, please choose a more elegant sentence.

5
On the second day of the Lunar New Year, the traditional New Year dinner with relatives in the village was canceled.
On the fifth day of the New Year, there was a disturbance in the village.
After dinner, I heard my aunt, my mother and my brother-in-law discussing the matter. The leader of the riot is considered to be a descendant, and in the village he can also be said to be a nephew of his grandmother. Originally, we do not intend to tell grandma, the first month in such a thing, people will be sentenced to detention for more than 10 days, is always unlucky. But later grandma still know, sitting on the Sofa, I saw her with a cracked right hand rubbed his eyes.
Grandmother every day is not sitting at the Mahjong table, or sitting in the living room watching the central three sets of TV programs, like those singing, dancing columns. Her information about the outbreak is mostly based on what we tell her.
The cause of trouble in the village is also related to the epidemic, said the police to commandeer a place in the village as a checkpoint, persuade people to return home this time. The man was drunk that day, refused to agree, not only not to set up positions, but also pushed, attacked the police, was quickly taken away.
A five-seater police car, with an alarm, drove past in a puff of smoke on the only road leading from the village to the outside. The entire village began to see the handling of the outbreak as a high-level emergency.
Cousin is still like a pioneer, from twenty-nine, will be on call from the state. Several important departments in the county have divided their respective dry areas, responsible for checking the physical condition and movement of people in the area. In the public's propaganda, education, management of the command, also do not relax, "do not relay in the wechat group without official certification on the content of the COVID-19, " also as one of the deliberately ordered.
One day, there were a total of 12 redheads updated, each with the same total file name, but the serial numbers in brackets ran from 1 to 12, and the last updated version was sent at 11 p.m.
I asked my cousin, do you usually receive so many documents in a day.
She said such workloads have been the norm since poverty alleviation began in 2017.

Anti poverty slogans still visible in the countryside
6
Later, the county that suspected illness did not have a diagnosis, cousin was relieved.
But also heard that the next county, there is a monk from Hubei back, before the festival in the temple set a few tables fete, county a mother and son to go on an appointment. As a result, the monk himself was diagnosed with COVID-19, and all who went to dinner that day were classified as "close contacts. ".
If it does spread, the mother and son will still be in the core area of the county. The virus is close at hand. It sent everyone back into a state of panic.
My aunt was also half a Buddhist believers, New Year's Day two will go to the temple worship. Before the Chinese New Year, she heard that the temple was temporarily closed because of the epidemic, and there was no special emotion, this year she "cloud lights" , has been on the mobile phone worship.
I found out that my mother spent at least two hours in bed swiping her cell phone every night this holiday season before falling asleep. Every day, she would wake up and look at the real time data of the epidemic, and tell me how many new people were added today, or the latest news from Zhejiang and Shanghai.
I heard whispers, too, for example, when people around me talk about it, they will say, "how could that monk from Hubei be so evil-minded and come out to harm others? " "these ordinary people dare to gather together for dinner at such an unusual time? " "It's a good thing that the family didn't come back for the New Year this year. They are also dangerous people from Hubei. ".
Sometimes you feel uncomfortable hearing those words, but understand that the speaker is not really afraid of "e" or discrimination against outsiders. They would say that because there are some things they do not understand, why Wuhan? Why Hubei? How did it get out? On such a massive scale, until now it seems like it's out of control.
Who pulled the trigger and put the bullet here.

7
My hometown has been a city of little change for more than ten years.
On a county scale, there are only five supermarkets, one Xinhua Bookstore, no high speed rail, no KFC, mcdonald's, starbucks. The biggest change in recent years has been the arrival of two private cinemas. This year, because of the impact of the epidemic, the cinema closed completely, the recovery time has not been determined.
Every now and then I feel like the city has aged since I was a child. It's not like Shanghai, where every block is replaced by new storefronts every year to renew the city's cells and new landmarks and buildings are being built. If anything were to change in this country, my hometown would be among the slowest to be affected.
But in this case, the alert state I felt was rapidly developing within a few days. In contrast to the Red Cross's ineptitude, the state apparatus's finely honed grip has emerged in recent days, reaching out quickly to the poorest of the poor.
By February 1, all the county roads leading to the countryside were blocked by blocking and stopping. Checkpoints into and out of the city were set up to persuade them to return. All the residential area also stands a piece of stick red paper writing brush notice, "non-residents of the residential area shall not enter. ". On 3 February, more roadblocks were erected at intersections and controls were tightened. My mother and I went out and back again.

Our eyes are still stopped in "Wuhan" , but the city is not just a Wuhan, including my hometown, this 18-line county, to a kind of blind speed, more thoroughly implemented than Shanghai.
I had written about these days in my diary, intending to use the word "martial law" , which I later looked up to refer to the military's use of the term to maintain stability. This is what disenchanted that generation of young people decades ago. Born into the 1990s, my knowledge of the "battle" is largely a matter of textual experience, of obscure books and Old News gleaned from the Internet that tell us about the suffering of the past. But now we have to accept a new reorganization of who we are.

The state of affairs has evolved so far, and is no longer reversible is the nation from the bottom up, people's panic. It forms a huge shaking force at the base of the building, exposing a delicate-looking Pagoda to the appearance of a crumbling wall. But perhaps a few days later, the pagoda will not collapse, it will become a myth.
It was only in teetering situations that I saw people finally begin to crave news coverage as desperately as they would a survival guide.
Because we live in an environment where we have to decide if we're going to survive.
I feel no sense of relief in a small town that is still COVID-19, and I am still surrounded by fear every day. Those who live in the dust can never speak for the infected, the broken hearts, the desperate souls, the departed lives.
But on the uninfected side, amid the anxiety of the message, the fear of uncertainty, and the political metaphors that are everywhere, we see for ourselves the long shadow of death on the ground. No one is immune to this era.

I feel no sense of relief in a small town that is still COVID-19, and I am still surrounded by fear every day. Those who live in the dust can never speak for the infected, the broken hearts, the desperate souls, the departed lives.

But on the uninfected side, amid the anxiety of the message, the fear of uncertainty, and the political metaphors that are everywhere, we see for ourselves the long shadow of death on the ground. No one is immune to this era.
